  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/5827",
  "title": "feat(server): add experimental support for React Server Components and Next.js app directory",
  "body": "Took a lot of inspiration from https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-client-nextjs\r\n\r\nHowever I found that if we call `use` only server-side without a `<Suspense>` boundary, we can completely render the page on the server without needing JS to swap the `<template>` tags like it does in their Client Components examples. We'll still have to see with Meta DevRel if it's okay to do 😅\r\n\r\nThe way I see it, it could be packaged as: \r\n- Either a stable or beta version of React InstantSearch which supports RSC, basically just the code calling `use` in `useWidget` and probably a new context.\r\n- A package for Next.js which would expose a component based on `<InstantSearch>`, which would also take care of injecting the initial results by directly importing the context from `next/navigation`, and retrieving them when client-side.\r\n\r\nUsers would simply have to use something like `<NextInstantSearch>` instead of `<InstantSearch>`, with the exact same options.",
